DATA CLOUD
Publish a Segment in Data Cloud

After defining your segment in Data Cloud, you can publish it to your activation targets whenever you want or based on a schedule when the segment was created. The standard publish schedule is 12 or 24 hours. You can also change the segment schedule by editing its properties. When you’ve reached the segment publish concurrency limit, Data Cloud defers the publish of other segments. This deferral continues until the number of simultaneously running segments falls below the limit. This means that a segment scheduled at a specific time sometimes doesn’t start publishing at its scheduled time.

In Data Cloud, go to Segments.
Select your segment from the list.
On the segment details page, to have the activation target pick up the segment, click the dropdown menu and select Publish Now.
The amount of time it takes to publish the segment depends on your volume and activation target. To see when the segment was published, check the Publish History page. To schedule publishing, edit the segment’s properties.
Increase Segment Refresh from Data Cloud to the Activation Targets
Increase the frequency of segment refresh and shorten publishing time for activations from Data Cloud to the activation targets using rapid segment publish. When you create a segment, choose a 1-hour or 4-hour schedule to send activation data, as compared to a standard 12-hour or 24-hour schedule. Each segment filters only the past 7 days of engagement data. Any records outside this window aren’t considered when selecting your output values.
Segment Types and Statuses
Learn more about the values provided about each segment. View details in the Segments section of Data Cloud, or in Publish History for a specific segment. Depending on how you create the segment, the type can be UI (created via the Segment Builder), Lookalike (created via a seed segment), or DBT (created via the API).
